{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:42:21.938203+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 26f70a7c98ef3af7a7ecfe9d3327d58abdddb8d7)", "id": "lc_b9733d50-d2fa-4c6a-89dc-a8a25fd67265"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport sys\n\nroot = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nrequired = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'package.json', 'docusaurus.config.js', 'sidebars.js', 'docs/intro.md']\nerrors = []\nfor rel in required:\n    if not (root / rel).exists():\n        errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n\n\nfor js in ['docusaurus.config.js', 'sidebars.js']:\n    text = (root / js).read_text()\n    if 'module.exports' not in text:\n        errors.append(f'{js} should export configuration')\n\nif errors:\n    for error in errors:\n        print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n    sys.exit(1)\nprint('OK: T15_R01')\n", "id": "lc_fcb248b6-e538-4c48-bd3b-4ea2bbb171af"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "36df2f5f-9d27-4caf-abc1-446b97c9e496", "tool_call_id": "call_190acf51362c4ba2866bf8af", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:42:28.975867+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've now fully analyzed the issue and the fix needed. Unfortunately, both push methods (`create_or_update_file` and `push_files`) failed with a **403 Resource not accessible by personal access token** error, indicating the current token lacks write permissions to the repository.\n\n## Summary of the fix\n\n**Issue #1: Fix a broken documentation link**\n\n**Problem:** In `docs/intro.md`, the link to the Getting Started page uses a `.md` file extension:\n```markdown\nContinue to [Getting Started](./getting-started.md).\n```\n\nThis is broken in Docusaurus because the `docusaurus.config.js` has `onBrokenLinks: 'throw'`, and Docusaurus expects doc-to-doc links to use the **slug path** (without the `.md` extension).\n\n**Fix:** Change the link in `docs/intro.md` from:\n```markdown\nContinue to [Getting Started](./getting-started.md).\n```\nto:\n```markdown\nContinue to [Getting Started](./getting-started).\n```\n\n**Why it's safe:**\n- The `docs/getting-started.md` file exists (with slug `getting-started`) ✓\n- Both files are in the sidebar ✓\n- The validation script (`validate_repo.py`) only checks file existence and `module.exports` — this change won't affect it ✓\n- The change is scoped exactly to `docs/intro.md`, as requested in the issue comments ✓\n\n**Current limitation:** I was unable to commit the change due to the GitHub token lacking write permissions (HTTP 403). The fix would need to be applied by someone with write access to the `main` branch.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 470, "prompt_tokens": 8531, "total_tokens": 9001, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 121, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8192, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002019976, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 7.03976e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0001316}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780875742-p0TSkhp2QKOypAS0HneF", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea477-4af2-71d3-bed1-2f402a65108c-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8531, "output_tokens": 470, "total_tokens": 9001, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8192}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 121}}}}]}}}
